+# OwOCloak Windows
+
+Frontend-first desktop VPN client shell for Windows, built with Flutter.
+
+## What is in this starter
+
+- Simple mode with one main connect action
+- Advanced mode with separate paths for self-hosted and team infrastructure
+- Personal cabinet UI with mock account data
+- Clean separation between UI, state, and mock data
+
+## Project structure
+
+- `lib/app` — app shell, theme, routing
+- `lib/core` — shared models and mock data
+- `lib/features` — feature screens
+
+## Current scope
+
+This repository is frontend-only for now.
+There is no real VPN backend, tunnel engine, or provisioning logic yet.
+
+## Next step
+
+Open the repo in VS Code or Positron, apply the patch, then run:
+
+```bash
+git add .
+git commit -m "Initial Flutter scaffold"
+```
+
+Later, when Flutter is installed, the app can be launched with:
+
+```bash
+flutter pub get
+flutter run -d windows
+```
